text: Kly Mod 16-7: CB 7 tripped again. Thyratron reservoir is @ 10.7 volts. Lowered res to 9 volts: station on, but PFN and BV waveforms very unstable. This thyratron is close to EOL. Removed Triton F-241 thyratron and replaced with L4888 removed from spare mod 02-7 (located next to 16-4). Last recorded reservoir volts on 02-7 tube was 4.1 volts. Station comes up and is now stable with reservoir @ 4.36 volts. L4888 in = 100680; F-241 out = 931. HV RTM = 59928 hrs. MM = 12.8%. KA = 268 mA. DQ I = 14 amps. HV = 17.2 KV @ .95 amps. CATER ready to close.

title: * Re: ****start looking at FACET - Fixed BC11 feedback with Glen's help, see details inside
text: First we noticed that the feedback was not regulating correctly (see figure 3). To troubleshoot this issue, Glen had us check the solid state sub-booster controls for 11-1 and 11-2 and look at the DAC Volts to see if the Phase and Amplitude Setpoints were updating. At the time, the DAC volts were not they were frozen at some values around 5.010V (see figure 2). To make these DAC volts update, Glen had us check the CALCOUT PVs that are associated with this feedback. To find those PVs go to Matlab GUIs -> Matlab PVs -> ML00 -> Matlab CALCOUT PVs -> ML00 001-050. Then we checked the edit panel in the 4 PVs labeled F2_Feedback. Each one of these PVs should have a scan rate of 0.5 seconds, but it was set to PASSIVE. To fix the feedback we set each of these F2_Feedback PV scan rates to 0.5 second (see figure 1 for an example of one of the PVs).

title: Kly Mods 16-4, 17-6, 18-3: various fault conditions, FLKs, etc.
text: 16-4: experienced some klystron vac faults and FLKd. Reset, station back on. 17-6: CB 7 tripped. Lowered res from 5.025 volts to 4.95. Statiion back on. 18-3: FLK'd, don't know why. K13 would not reset armature back to 0 position. Sprayed relay with contact cleaner: reset to zero and station back on. Monitored for a while: no faults.

title: * Re: ****start looking at FACET - made a strip tool to help monitor BC11 feedback regulation
text: I added the DAC volts and the scan rate of those matlab PVs. The DAC volts should have some slow oscillation, and the SCAN rate should be set to 0.5 second which corresponds to a numeric value of 7. If the DAC volts flatline and the SCAN rate shows a numeric value of 0, then follow the steps to restore the scan rate for these PVs to 0.5 second. The filename is bc11_feedback_params.stp, feel free to add more PVs for monitoring this feedback if needed.

text: Reset station. Ranged thyratron from 4.1 to 4.2 volts. Found high limit @ 4.35 volts. Raised DQ current from 13 amps to 14 amps to get BV down. In this process, fault counter (K13 old style counter) counted up at least 5 faults. After lowering BV by raising DQ I, no more fault counts.
